abstract: As Renewal, the mayor’s signature education program, enters its fourth school year, results are mixed at best and the city must decide the fate of schools taking part.
snippet: As Renewal, the mayor’s signature education program, enters its fourth school year, results are mixed at best and the city must decide the fate of schools taking part.
lead_paragraph: Even as New York City’s schools opened their doors for the new year this month, the clock was ticking on the future of Mayor Bill de Blasio’s boldest education initiative.

abstract: While many players and owners rebuked President Trump’s comments on protests, ratings declines could mean trouble for broadcasters and sponsors.
snippet: While many players and owners rebuked President Trump’s comments on protests, ratings declines could mean trouble for broadcasters and sponsors.
lead_paragraph: The biggest clash in the N.F.L. over the weekend was off the field — but the battle over protests may soon draw in the broadcasters, deep-pocketed sponsors who partner with the league as well.

abstract: Barry Diller was about to win the battle for his $250 million arts pier, but then came the “petty questions” from his opponents and he decided to pull the plug.
snippet: Barry Diller was about to win the battle for his $250 million arts pier, but then came the “petty questions” from his opponents and he decided to pull the plug.
lead_paragraph: For Barry Diller, the turning point came at a Sept. 5 settlement meeting with the small band of opponents who had tied up his plans for a $250 million park and cultural center in the Hudson River for more than two years.

abstract: The move by the British capital’s transportation regulator is a significant setback, as the ride-hailing service deals with trouble on multiple fronts.
snippet: The move by the British capital’s transportation regulator is a significant setback, as the ride-hailing service deals with trouble on multiple fronts.
lead_paragraph: Transport for London, the city’s transportation regulator, said on Friday that it would not renew the ride-hailing service’s operating license when it expires on Sept. 30.

abstract: Its move to hire HTC engineers is intended to improve competition with Apple and Samsung. But the tech giant’s previous foray into handset making did not go so well.

abstract: In a symbolic passing of the guard, Mr. Clinton will be the first speaker Wednesday at the Bloomberg Global Business Forum.
snippet: In a symbolic passing of the guard, Mr. Clinton will be the first speaker Wednesday at the Bloomberg Global Business Forum.
lead_paragraph: For more than a decade, the Clinton Global Initiative was the star-studded marquee attraction during the annual meeting of the United Nations General Assembly, a place where heads of state, celebrities, billionaire philanthropists and business people mingled, made deals and gave away millions, sometimes billions, of dollars.

abstract: The bankruptcy filing by Toys “R” Us shows just how much pain store operators are feeling — and highlighted that more suffering is in store.
snippet: The bankruptcy filing by Toys “R” Us shows just how much pain store operators are feeling — and highlighted that more suffering is in store.
lead_paragraph: If you’re a retailer and you’re not Amazon or Walmart, life can be very hard. The bankruptcy filing by Toys “R” Us on Monday is just the latest example.

abstract: Facebook, Google and other technology titans are encountering more resistance to their empire-building, both abroad and at home.
snippet: Facebook, Google and other technology titans are encountering more resistance to their empire-building, both abroad and at home.
lead_paragraph: For a long time, American technology giants have received a chilly reception from skeptical audiences in Europe, including from government regulators, while at home, companies like Google, Facebook and Amazon have been largely lauded for their innovation and their astonishing growth.
